{
  "text": "It is also important to point out the difference between an SPA, MSA, or EMS decoding iteration and a stochastic decoding iteration. In the former case during one iteration the nodes exchange full pmf messages, while in the stochastic case only one symbol is exchanged per edge. To emphasize this difference, the stochastic decoding iteration is referred to as a decoding cycle (DC) [CITATION_1] .",
